{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1775048846,"nonce":"Y0GeE2T7dQjbpy0TyWLJFiFu4w8=","title":"Logo should not be h1 on every page","message":"The site logo/brand 'Bonanza' is rendered as an h1 on every page (#logo in application.sass.scss). This is semantically incorrect — h1 should be the page's main topic, not a repeated site-wide element.\n\nThe logo should use a non-heading element (e.g. a link, span, or div). Each page should have its own h1 reflecting its actual content (e.g. 'Ausleihbedingungen', 'Datenschutz', the borrower name on detail pages, etc.).\n\nThis also creates a broken heading hierarchy: the page-level headings (currently h2/h3) sit below a logo h1 that has nothing to do with the page content.","files":null}]}